<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182002" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">Pheidole scalaris</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182002" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">scalaris</taxonomicName>
, of a ladder, alluding to the strong ladder-like pattern on the dorsum of the major head. diagnosis Close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
but distinguished from it and other members of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
group by the broad occipital zone of rugoreticulum on the dorsal surface of the head of the major, surmounting a wide &quot;ladder&quot; of parallel transverse carinulae that reach the frontal lobes, where they curve anteriorly to the ends of the lobes; also, the premesonotal dorsum is completely covered by transverse carinulae. Also, see the distinctive color of the minor (below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">
This species is possibly synonymous with 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151610" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata nigridens Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata nigridens Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="transversostriata" variety="nigridens">P. transversostriata var. nigridens</taxonomicName>
Forel of Colombia, which has been provisionally synonymized with 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:151610" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata nigridens Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata nigridens Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigridens">nigridens</taxonomicName>
has rugoreticula on the occipital corners and more carinulae on the pronotal dorsum, and is intermediate between 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182002" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">scalaris</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182002" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">scalaris</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
by the more elongate head of the major (Head Length 1.3X Head Width versus 1.2X in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole transversostriata Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversostriata">transversostriata</taxonomicName>
) and smooth sides of the pronotum of the minor. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.64, HL 0.84, SL 0.32, EL 0.10, PW 0.36. Paratype minor: HW 0.42, HL 0.46, SL 0.36, EL 0.08, PW 0.26. Color Major: concolorous medium yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="643">Minor: overall light brownish yellow, with medium brown vertex, occiput, and dorsum of promesonotum, and medium yellow appendages.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">Range Atlantic and northern Pacific lowlands of Costa Rica; and Arima Valley, Trinidad.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="643">
Biology Longino (1997) found 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182002" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scalaris Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">P. scalaris</taxonomicName>
in both seasonal dry forest and evergreen forest. The workers were recruited to baits on the forest floor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
